# Cursor Rules — The JS & TS Fun Book

You are working on **The JS & TS Fun Book**, an interactive single-page HTML tutorial for learning TypeScript, NestJS, React, and fullstack development.

## Project Structure

```
js-ts-fun-book/
├── index.html                    ← Redirect to the-js-ts-fun-book.html
├── the-js-ts-fun-book.html       ← Rendering engine (CSS + HTML + JS, ~40KB)
├── data.js                       ← Lesson content (30 lessons, ~128KB)
├── README.md                     ← Project description
└── CLAUDE.md                     ← Full project documentation (READ THIS FIRST)
```

## Critical Rules

1. **Always read `CLAUDE.md` first** — It contains the full architecture, data schema, design system, and all function documentation.

2. **Two-file architecture**: `the-js-ts-fun-book.html` is the engine, `data.js` is the content. They are separate files connected via `<script src="data.js">`.

3. **data.js exports a global**: `const LESSONS_DATA = [...]` — Do NOT change this to ES modules, CommonJS, or any other format.

4. **Quiz property is `q:` not `t:`** — Each quiz uses `{ q: "question", opts: [...], ans: Number }`. Using `t:` instead of `q:` is a known past bug.

5. **Exactly 3 quizzes per lesson** — The achievement system depends on this. Don't add more or fewer.

6. **SVG icons only** — No emoji anywhere. All icons use `<svg>` with `stroke: currentColor`.

7. **Brand colors**: Accent = `#D9FE06` (neon green), Dark BG = `#12151A`, Font = Poppins.

8. **No external dependencies** except Google Fonts (Poppins). Everything is self-contained.

9. **ICONS map in HTML**: Keys `1`–`30` map to SVG strings. When adding lessons, add matching icons.

10. **Theme toggle**: Dark mode is default. Light mode via `html[data-theme="light"]`. Persisted in `localStorage`.

## When Editing Lessons (data.js)

Each lesson follows this exact schema:
```js
{
  id: Number,        // Sequential 1-30
  title: String,
  subtitle: String,
  analogy: String,   // Fun real-world analogy
  points: [          // 6-11 teaching points
    { t: String, d: String }
  ],
  whatIs: String,
  realWorld: String,
  code: String,      // Code example (use backtick template literals)
  funFact: String,   // Optional
  quiz: [            // EXACTLY 3 quizzes
    { q: String, opts: [String, String, String, String], ans: Number }
  ],
  challenge: String
}
```

## When Editing the Engine (the-js-ts-fun-book.html)

- CSS is in a single `<style>` block in `<head>`
- JS is in a single `<script>` block before `</body>`
- Key functions: `render()`, `goTo(i)`, `checkQuiz()`, `showAchievement()`, `spawnConfetti()`, `toggleTheme()`
- State variables: `current`, `completed` (Set), `codeVisible`, `quizScores`, `shownAchievements` (Set)

## Style Conventions

- Minified-ish CSS (one rule per line, short property names)
- Compact JS (minimal whitespace, arrow functions, template literals)
- HTML uses semantic elements: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`
- BEM-lite class naming: `.lesson-title`, `.quiz-btn`, `.achievement-card`

## Testing

After any change, verify:
- All 30 lessons render without errors
- All 90 quizzes have `q:` property (not `t:`)
- Each lesson has exactly 3 quiz items
- ICONS map has keys matching all lesson IDs
- Theme toggle works in both directions
- Achievement popup triggers after answering all 3 quizzes in a lesson
